# Supabase
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key

# These values come from your Supabase project settings
# Authentication → API → Project URL and anon public key
# Never commit the actual .env file — only this example file

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SERVER-ONLY — Paystack serverless functions (api/paystack/*)
# Set these in the Vercel dashboard (Project → Settings → Environment Variables),
# NOT in a local .env consumed by Vite. They must NEVER be VITE_-prefixed — a
# VITE_ prefix would bundle them into the client. Listed here only as documentation.
#
#   PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY          Paystack API auth AND webhook HMAC key (sk_test_… / sk_live_…)
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY    lets the webhook write subscriptions as service-role
#   SUPABASE_URL                 project URL for the functions (defaults to VITE_SUPABASE_URL)
#   PAYSTACK_PLAN_CODE_MONTHLY   PLN_ code for Pro Monthly (₵40/mo)
#   PAYSTACK_PLAN_CODE_ANNUAL    PLN_ code for Pro Annual  (₵400/yr)
#
# Note: Paystack signs webhooks with PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY — there is no separate
# webhook secret. Test and live modes use different keys AND different PLN_ codes.
